  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Is PET-CT scan better than PET or CT alone in diagnosing primary tumours in patients with
      unknown primary tumors? Can information obtained with PET-CT replace other clinical and
      radiological investigations? Is PET/CT cost-effective?
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients who fulfill the international definition of unknown primary tumors can be included,
      except:

        -  Young men (&lt;55 years) with growing mid-line tumors where a germ cell tumor could be
           expected will not be included.

        -  Patients with lymph-node metastases with squamous cell carcinoma in the head and neck
           region will not be included.

        -  Women with adenocarcinoma in lymph nodes in the axilla will not be included.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
